# Core Events Context

You are changing cross-domain EventBus/runtime event contracts (`GameEvents` in v0.x and runtime event interfaces/hubs).

Read these docs:

1. `docs/design/core-architecture.md` — EventBus pattern + current/planned `GameEvents` surface
2. `docs/design/README.md` — domain routing index to load only affected system docs
3. `docs/design/inventory-and-economy.md` when adding/changing inventory event contracts (`OnItemPickupRequested`, `OnItemStored`, `OnItemPickupRejected`, `OnBeltSelectionChanged`, `OnInventoryChanged`)
4. `docs/design/weapons-and-ballistics.md` when adding/changing weapon/shooting event contracts (`OnWeaponEquipped`, `OnWeaponFired`, `OnWeaponReloaded`, `OnProjectileHit`)

If an event shape change affects a domain payload/restore boundary, also load:

5. `docs/design/save-contract-quick-reference.md`
6. `docs/design/save-and-progression.md`

When adding new event groups or moving event-contract files across `Core/Scripts/Events` and `Core/Scripts/Runtime`, keep this router globs aligned in the same change.
